# NestJS Project - Master Rule Index

Central index for all Cursor rules defining development guidelines and best practices.

## Core Architecture

| Rule File              | Description                                                       |
| :--------------------- | :---------------------------------------------------------------- |
| @project-structure.mdc | Project structure and module organization                         |
| @decorators.mdc        | Common decorators (@CurrentUser, @Public, @Roles, @CustomTimeout) |

## Application Components

| Rule File                    | Description                                                          |
| :--------------------------- | :------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| @entity.mdc                  | TypeORM entities: structure, naming, relationships, standard fields  |
| @service-layers.mdc          | Service organization: domain separation, layering, method decomposition |
| @service-implementation.mdc  | Service implementation: DTOs, error handling, logging, dependencies  |
| @controller.mdc              | HTTP layer: routing, delegation to services, no business logic       |
| @repository.mdc              | Database access: use @InjectRepository, no custom repositories       |
| @dto.mdc                     | Data Transfer Objects: validation, transformation, serialization     |
| @types.mdc                   | Type definitions: interfaces, type aliases, enums (non-DTO/Entity)  |

## WebSocket Components

| Rule File             | Description                                                                     |
| :-------------------- | :------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| @gateway.mdc          | WebSocket gateway: event handlers, SocketService integration, lifecycle hooks  |
| @socket-service.mdc   | Socket business logic: event emissions, room management, disconnection handling |

## Infrastructure

| Rule File            | Description                                          |
| :------------------- | :--------------------------------------------------- |
| @logger.mdc          | Winston-based logging service usage                  |
| @pagination.mdc      | Pagination implementation with shared infrastructure |
| @domain-exception.mdc| Domain exceptions: error handling, error codes, best practices |

## Usage

1. Follow guidelines when implementing new features
2. Reference rules using @ symbol (e.g., @entity.mdc)
3. Update rules when introducing new patterns
